subdefinitions.definition: A town in Moray council area, Scotland , United Kingdom , the original place from which the others were named.
A large valley southeast of Cape Town , South Africa .

A number of places in Canada : An unincorporated community in the Rural Municipality of Grassland , Manitoba . A rural community and parish in Albert County , New Brunswick . A community in Pictou County , Nova Scotia . A hamlet in Rideau Lakes , Ontario . A county in Ontario ; see Elgin County . A rural municipality in Quebec .

A number of places in the United States : An unincorporated community in Lauderdale County , Alabama . A census-designated place in Santa Cruz County , Arizona . A ghost town in Merced County , California . A city in Cook County and Kane County , Illinois . A township in Kane County , Illinois . A tiny city in Fayette County , Iowa . A tiny city in Chautauqua County , Kansas . A small city and township in Wabasha County , Minnesota . An unincorporated community in Shelby County , Missouri . A minor city and township in Antelope County , Nebraska . A ghost town in Nevada . A tiny city in Grant County , North Dakota . A village in Van Wert County , Ohio . A small city in Comanche County , Oklahoma . A small city in Union County , Oregon . A borough in Erie County , Pennsylvania . An incorporated town in Kershaw County , South Carolina . A census-designated place in Lancaster County , South Carolina . A census-designated place and unincorporated community in Scott County , Tennessee . A city in Bastrop County and Travis County , Texas . A neighborhood of Green River , Emery County , Utah .
A rural locality in the Shire of Capel , Western Australia .
